.Dd $Mdocdate: July 5 2009 $
.Dt RADEONFB 4 sparc64
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm radeonfb
.Nd accelerated color frame buffer
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Cd "radeonfb* at pci?"
.Cd "wsdisplay* at radeonfb?"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
driver supports Sun PCI frame buffer cards based on the
ATI
.Sq Radeon
chips, such as the
Sun
XVR-100
and
XVR-300
boards.
It does not provide direct device driver entry points
but makes its functions available via the internal
.Xr wsdisplay 4
interface.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr intro 4 ,
.Xr pci 4 ,
.Xr wscons 4 ,
.Xr wsdisplay 4
@


1.1
log
@radeonfb(4), an accelerated framebuffer for Sun XVR-100 boards (which have an
ATI Radeon 7000 chip on them).  While there, make gfxp(4) depend on rasops32
just in case somebody removes other framebuffers that pull this in from their
kernel config.

